#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.190"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.190:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.190:0.2"
msgid "19. Brāhmaṇavagga "
msgstr "19. Brahmins "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: bhikkhusaṅghathomanasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.190:0.3"
msgid "190. Uposathasutta "
msgstr "190. Sabbath "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.190:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.190:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā tadahuposathe bhikkhusaṃghaparivuto nisinno hoti. "
msgstr "Now, at that time it was the sabbath, and the Buddha was sitting surrounded by the Saṅgha of monks. "

msgctxt "an4.190:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tuṇhībhūtaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ anuviloketvā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha looked around the Saṅgha of monks, who were so very silent. He addressed them: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.190:2.1"
msgid "“Apalāpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā nippalāpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā suddhā sāre patiṭṭhitā. "
msgstr "“This assembly has no nonsense, mendicants, it’s free of nonsense. It consists purely of the essential core. "

msgctxt "an4.190:2.2"
msgid "Tathārūpo ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhusaṃgho, tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā. "
msgstr "Such is this Saṅgha of monks, such is this assembly! "

msgctxt "an4.190:2.3"
msgid "Yathārūpā parisā dullabhā dassanāyapi lokasmiṃ, tathārūpo ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhusaṃgho, tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā. "
msgstr "An assembly such as this is rarely seen in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.190:2.4"
msgid "Yathārūpā parisā āhuneyyā pāhuneyyā dakkhiṇeyyā añjalikaraṇīyā anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa, tathārūpo ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhusaṃgho, tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā. "
msgstr "An assembly such as this is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world. "

msgctxt "an4.190:2.5"
msgid "Yathārūpāya parisāya appaṃ dinnaṃ bahu hoti bahu dinnaṃ bahutaraṃ, tathārūpo ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhusaṃgho, tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā. "
msgstr "Even a small gift to an assembly such as this is plentiful, while giving more is even more plentiful. "

#. VAR: tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā → etthantare pāṭho sī, syā1-3, kaṃ, pā1 potthakesu
msgctxt "an4.190:2.6"
msgid "Yathārūpaṃ parisaṃ alaṃ yojanagaṇanānipi dassanāya gantuṃ api puṭosenāpi, tathārūpo ayaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhusaṃgho, tathārūpāyaṃ, bhikkhave, parisā. "
msgstr "An assembly such as this is worth traveling many leagues to see, even if you have to carry your own provisions in a shoulder bag. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.184, sc3
msgctxt "an4.190:3.1"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, bhikkhū imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe devappattā viharanti; "
msgstr "There are monks staying in this Saṅgha who have attained to the gods. "

msgctxt "an4.190:3.2"
msgid "santi, bhikkhave, bhikkhū imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe brahmappattā viharanti; "
msgstr "There are monks staying in this Saṅgha who have attained to Brahmā. "

msgctxt "an4.190:3.3"
msgid "santi, bhikkhave, bhikkhū imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe āneñjappattā viharanti; "
msgstr "There are monks staying in this Saṅgha who have attained to the imperturbable. "

msgctxt "an4.190:3.4"
msgid "santi, bhikkhave, bhikkhū imasmiṃ bhikkhusaṅghe ariyappattā viharanti. "
msgstr "There are monks staying in this Saṅgha who have attained to nobility. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.190:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu devappatto hoti? "
msgstr "And how has a monk attained to the gods? "

msgctxt "an4.190:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati; "
msgstr "It’s when a monk, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption … "

msgctxt "an4.190:4.3"
msgid "vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption … "

msgctxt "an4.190:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu devappatto hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a monk has attained to the gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.190:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu brahmappatto hoti? "
msgstr "And how has a monk attained to Brahmā? "

msgctxt "an4.190:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "Firstly, a monk meditates spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

msgctxt "an4.190:5.3"
msgid "Karuṇā … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a monk meditates spreading a heart full of compassion … "

msgctxt "an4.190:5.4"
msgid "muditā … "
msgstr "rejoicing … "

msgctxt "an4.190:5.5"
msgid "upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ tathā tatiyaṃ tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

msgctxt "an4.190:5.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu brahmappatto hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a monk has attained to Brahmā. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.190:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āneñjappatto hoti? "
msgstr "And how has a monk attained to the imperturbable? "

msgctxt "an4.190:6.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a monk—going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity—aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space. "

msgctxt "an4.190:6.3"
msgid "Sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, he enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness. "

msgctxt "an4.190:6.4"
msgid "Sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, he enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness. "

msgctxt "an4.190:6.5"
msgid "Sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Going totally beyond the dimension of nothingness, he enters and remains in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. "

msgctxt "an4.190:6.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āneñjappatto hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a monk has attained to the imperturbable. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an4.190:7.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyappatto hoti? "
msgstr "And how has a monk attained to nobility? "

msgctxt "an4.190:7.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "It’s when they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’. "

msgctxt "an4.190:7.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ariyappatto hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how a monk has attained to nobility.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.190:7.4"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.190:7.5"
msgid "Brāhmaṇavaggo catuttho. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.185, sc8
msgctxt "an4.190:8.1"
msgid "Yodhā pāṭibhogasutaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.190:8.2"
msgid "Abhayaṃ brāhmaṇasaccena pañcamaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.190:8.3"
msgid "Ummaggavassakāro, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.190:8.4"
msgid "Upako sacchikiriyā ca uposathoti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
